cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.LO, cs.FL, cs.LG 

This paper presents a new approach to automated reasoning about higher-order programs using symbolic execution and behavioral contracts. The paper focuses on the operational semantics of programs with both concrete and symbolic components, which suggests that it is likely to be categorized under cs.PL (Programming Languages). The paper also discusses the use of contracts as symbolic values, which is a topic related to software engineering, suggesting that it could also be categorized under cs.SE (Software Engineering). The paper's focus on soundly predicting program behavior and contract correctness suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) and cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory). Finally, the paper's use of symbolic reasoning and existing program assertions suggests that it could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning).
